Group 1: Methylmethacrylate as a full thickness inlay.

Group 2: Methylmethacrylate as an onlay only.

In group 1 there were 32 patients for whom the average follow up was 8.2 years (range 2–16 years). In group 2 there were 66 patients with an average follow up of 7.1 years (range 2–20 years). After a minimum follow up of 2 years, 89 out of 98 of the patients retained their implants. Nine implants in total were removed. Of the 89 patients retaining their implants, 85 had excellent or good results at long-term follow up. The infection and implant removal rate was very high if nasal or frontal sinus tissue was in direct contact with the implant during the operative procedure.

