While satisfying the above requirements, our circuit offers state-of-the-art smallest area occupation (0.13 mm2) and consumes 4.5 [mu]W. Sub-threshold-biased lateral pnp transistors, used to implement very high resistance value integrated resistors, have been characterized to determine the resistance spread.
The fabricated prototype, coupled with a commercial Micro-Electrode Array ({MEA}), has been successfully employed to record the extracellular electrophysiological spontaneous activity, both of muscular cardiac cells (cardiomyocytes) and of spinal cord neurons from murines.},
