	abstract = {{PURPOSE}: The time-of-flight ({ToF}) technique is an emerging technique for rapidly acquiring distance information and is becoming increasingly popular for intra-operative surface acquisition. Using the {ToF} technique as an intra-operative imaging modality requires seamless integration into the clinical workflow. We thus aim to integrate {ToF} support in an existing framework for medical image processing.
